)attr default(%+_)
  _ type( input) intens(low ) just(left ) hilite(uscore)
  ~ type(text) intens(high) caps(off) just(asis ) hilite(reverse) color(turq)
  [ type(output) intens(high) caps(off) just(left) pas(on) skip(on)
)Body Expand(\\)
%Tutorial -\-\~The z ISPF Git Interface (zigi)%\-\- Tutorial
%Selection ===>_ZCMD                                                          +
+
                             %Config+or%Set
+
+The%Config+command displays, and then allows changing info used by ZIGI and Git
+
+Both user.name and user.email are required. These are used by Git commit.
+
+Also required is the number of generations to be enabled for the Partitioned
+Datasets. Anything from%0+to the system limit (default=0).
+
+The Point-and-Shoot defaults control what happens if a double-click or Enter
+occurs outside the table or on a table row.%P+displays the Options popup
+if outside the table or the Row Options popup if within the table.%S+
+does nothing if outside the table or default to select if within the table.
+
+Prompt before exiting ZIGI just in case.
+Bypass File Extension prompt when adding PDS Members is a global default.
+Bypass the ZIGI Splash screen for those who don't want to see it.
+
         +Press the%Enter+key to continue your ZIGI tutorial journey.
)Init
 .cursor  = &zcmd
)PROC
 &ZCONT = ZIGIH14A
)END
